<div id="review_3150862975" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3150862975" />
    <a title="Paul" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68029956-paul"><img alt="Paul" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552062265p2/68029956.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3150862975?book_show_action=true">Jan 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul" href="/user/show/68029956-paul">Paul</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68029956-paul?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68029956-paul?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/68029956-paul?shelf=non-art-photo">non-art-photo</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3150862975" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4316495502790128504">I think that people have generally misunderstood Freud; he is not anything remotely resembling a scientist, but rather a deeply untalented moral philosopher and cultural critic who inexplicably tried to use anecdotes from psychotherapy sessions as a quasi-‘scientific’ basis for his terrible ideas. <br/><br/>It’s sort of like Paul Krugman trying to dress up his half-assed political commentary under the mantle of “prize-winning economist”; one of these things has nothing to do with the other. <br/><br/>To be sure, Fr</span>
  <span id="freeText4316495502790128504" style="display:none">I think that people have generally misunderstood Freud; he is not anything remotely resembling a scientist, but rather a deeply untalented moral philosopher and cultural critic who inexplicably tried to use anecdotes from psychotherapy sessions as a quasi-‘scientific’ basis for his terrible ideas. <br /><br />It’s sort of like Paul Krugman trying to dress up his half-assed political commentary under the mantle of “prize-winning economist”; one of these things has nothing to do with the other. <br /><br />To be sure, Freud’s case studies have some limited value (therapist ‘transference’ is a real thing, for example) but <i>Discontents</i> is just a mess. If I wanted to read a third-rate Nietzsche, I'd just read Foucault -- at least he's sort of fun.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4316495502790128504" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
